eecalcs.conductors

Class MetalCond

  • java.lang.Object
    • eecalcs.conductors.MetalProp
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AluminumCond, CopperCond

    public class MetalCond
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the properties common to aluminum and copper conductors into a generic non metal-specific conductor. This class is to be supper class of metal-specific conductors like CopperCond and AluminumCond

    • Constructor Detail

      • MetalCond

        public MetalCond(int amp60,
                 int amp75,
                 int amp90,
                 double resInPVCCond,
                 double resInALCond,
                 double resInSteelCond)
        Constructs a generic conductor object with common to aluminum and copper conductors
        Parameters:
        amp60 - The ampacity of this generic conductor with an insulation rated for 60°C
        amp75 - The ampacity of this generic conductor with an insulation rated for 75°C
        amp90 - The ampacity of this generic conductor with an insulation rated for 90°C
        resInPVCCond - The AC resistance of this generic conductor when used in a PVC conduit
        resInALCond - The AC resistance of this generic conductor when used in an aluminum conduit
        resInSteelCond - The AC resistance of this generic conductor when used in a steel conduit

    • Method Detail

      • getAmpacity

        public int getAmpacity(int temperature)
        Returns the ampacity of this generic conductor for the given temperature rating
        Parameters:
        temperature - The temperature rating of the conductor's insulation
        Returns:
        The ampacity as per NEC 2014 table 310.15(B)(16) or zero if the temperature is not 60 or 75 or 90 degrees Celsius

      • getACResistance

        public double getACResistance(Material material)
        Returns the AC resistance of this generic conductor when used in a conduit given's material
        Parameters:
        material - The material of the conduit
        Returns:
        The AC resistance in ohms per 1000 feet

      • getACResistance

        public double getACResistance(Material material,
                              double oneWayLength,
                              int numberOfSets)
        Returns the total resistance of this generic conductor for the given conduit material, length and number of parallel conductors
        Parameters:
        material - Conductor material as defined by Material
        oneWayLength - The length of the conductor in feet
        numberOfSets - The number of conductors in parallel
        Returns:
        The total AC resistance
